ol woodman founded two startups both of which never fully made it off the ground the first was a website called empowerallcom which attempted to sell electronic goods for no more than a  markup and the second was funbug a gaming and marketing platform that gave users the chance to win cash prizes woodman took the lack of success from both companies personally after failing to reach success on his own nick went home and received a  investment from his father an investment banker in silicon valley  and used his parents connections to venture capital to launch his career as the head of gopro careeredit while on hiatus in australia and indonesia on a surf trip he used a mm camera attached to the palm of his hand by a rubber band to try to capture his surfing activities on film seeing that amateur photographers like him – who wanted to capture quality action photos of their activities – had difficulties because either they could not get close enough to the action or were unable to purchase quality equipment at affordable prices his trip became his inspiration to found gopro his solution was to develop a belt that would attach the camera to the body woodman and his future wife jill financed the business by selling shell necklaces they bought in bali for  from their car along the california coast for  his mother loaned him  and let him borrow her sewing machine which he used to sew camera straps while experimenting with early designs his dad loaned him an additional  which woodman immediately paid back out of company sales his desire for a camera system that could capture close up footage inspired the gopro name the original cameras he developed were pointandshoot mm film cameras which mounted to the users wrist woodman would go about selling his products while using his  volkwagen bus that he named the buscuit as his mobile home the product has since evolved into a compact digital camera that supports wifi can be remotely controlled has waterproof housing records to a micro sd card and is affordable to the average action sports enthusiast – woodman would often act as the test engineer for their earlier products completing tasks such as attaching a gopro to a car and driving at speeds of over  mph in  he made his first big sale when a japanese company ordered  cameras at a sports show thereafter sales doubled every year and in  gopro sold  million cameras in  woodman appeared on qvc to sell his gopro hero in  gopro had about  in revenue which grew to about  in  in december  the taiwanese contract manufacturer foxconn purchased  of the company for  million which set the market value of the company at  billion making woodman who owned the majority of the stock a billionaire on june   gopro went public – closing the day at  a share in  woodman was the highest paid us chief executive paying himself  million in  gopro developed a partnership with the nhl that would enable the nhl to use gopro products to improve the viewing experience for fans woodman has been invited to speak at various tech conferences and in october  woodman was a guest on the late show with stephen colbert and wore a gopro camera for the entirety of the interview woodman is set to appear as a shark investor in the sixth season of the show shark tank woodman has invested  as of november  on shark tank on two investments at the beginning of  gopro started to make a series of job cuts in january of  woodmans company cut  jobs or  of his workforce later that year in november  gopro cut an additional  of the gopro workforce after attempting to branch out beyond its core business of action cameras as the entertainment division failed to reach profitability in december  a class action lawsuit against gopro was announced the complaint alleges that gopro made false and misleading statements to investors andor failed to disclose flaws in the companys drones overstating customer demand and gopros public statements were materially false and misleading   proved to be a tough year for gopro with the many changes at and involving gopro including numerous job cuts and falling stock prices woodman was listed as one of the years worst ceos  awardsedit  national award winner of the ey entrepreneur of the year award  winner of the technology and engineering emmy award in the category of inexpensive small rugged hd camcorders woodman brought his gopro onstage for his acceptance speech philanthropyedit after a successful ipo the couple donated  million shares of gopro stock to the jill  nicholas woodman foundation a new fund they created at the silicon valley community foundation in   from  to  the value of the stock donated declined from  million to  million because of the dramatic decline in gopro stock woodman was one of the biggest donors in the tech industry that year however it angered investors in march  woodman was honored for his philanthropic work with build at their th annual gala in san francisco personal lifeedit woodman is married to jill r scully and they have three children they live in woodside california woodman is known as the mad billionaire due to his unconventional behavior and eccentricities woodman is a strong believer in following ones passions as a way to success stating i’m a big believer that when you’re pursuing your passions your best ideas come to you your passions are a bit like your fingerprints everybody has them everybody’s are different one’s passions may just be a guidebook to one’s life” in  woodman hosted an ama on reddit woodman has often cited his fear of failure as a catalyst for his success stating when i got out of college i gave myself till i was  to invent a product if i couldnt do it by then i would just get a real job and that fear – the fear of a real job – motivated me to be an entrepreneur in december  woodman commissioned a foot yacht estimated to cost between  million and  million the boat expected to be delivered in  is four decks high and comes with a jacuzzi pool swim platform sweeping sun decks and dining areas  referencesedit  gopro ceo nick woodman is no longer a billionaire again as gopro stock drops  after hours forbescom  retrieved    how gopro ceo nick woodman let consumers lead him to new idea adagecom july   retrieved september     a b c wall street journal how family ties helped nick woodman make gopro click by lizette chapman june    with dad dean woodmanand stepdad us venture partners general partner irwin federman  a b acg silicon valley irwin federman us venture partners retrieved may    he federman has been married to the former concepcion socarras since   san francisco social diary new york social diary january   retrieved january     bay area billionaires  – explore san francisco blog exploresanfranciscobiz february   retrieved january     alum gives moses brown  million for performingarts community center the providence journal archived from the original on october   retrieved september     brett gavin february   how gopro cameras have made nothing unfilmable by the man who invented them the telegraph retrieved june     robehmed natalie september   the youngest billionaires on the forbes   under  yahoo finance retrieved october     a b the best ride of our lives uc san diego triton retrieved october     lipton josh july   meet gopros thrillseeking founder nick woodman cnbc retrieved october     a b the biscuit nick woodmans  volkswagen bus – in photos the early years of gopro and founder nicholas woodman forbes retrieved november     a b c forbes the worlds billionaires – nicholas woodman september   a b c d e f g h i welcome to the billionaires club by orna taub jewish business news march    mac ryan march   five startup lessons from gopro founder and billionaire nick woodman forbes retrieved june     leo sun  is gopro inc ceo nick woodman worth  million  san antonio expressnews mmysanantoniocom retrieved    woodmans family became millionaires business insider  retrieved    chapman lizette  how family ties helped nick woodman make gopro 