d over  from his parents to invest in the business in  the company sold its first camera system which used  mm film digital still and video cameras were later introduced as of update a fixedlens hd video camera with a wide degree lens was available two or more can be paired to create  video on june   the company announced the appointment of former microsoft executive tony bates as president reporting directly to woodman in january  gopro partnered with periscope for live streaming after growing the number of employees by more than  in  the company responded to weak sales in the fourth quarter by cutting about  of its workforce  workers in january  at its peak a share of gopro was valued at  but on september   only  in november  the company announced it was laying off an additional  employees in an effort to reduce costs the company also announced that president tony bates would be stepping down at the end of  corporate actionsedit on march   gopro acquired cineform the acquisition included the cineform  video codec used in the film slumdog millionaire the company claimed that the codec makes hd and d editing faster and more convenient without sacrificing image quality it was incorporated in the companys d hero system shortly after the acquisition in march  gopro issued a dmca takedown notice to website digitalrevcom which had posted a review of its product citing trademark use as a breach of copyright this notice was retracted  days later citing erroneous enforcement on february   gopro spent  million and acquired two startups namely stupeflix and vemory for their video editing tools replay and splice ipoedit on february   gopro submitted a confidential filing for an initial public offering ipo with the securities and exchange commission sec on may   gopro filed its s with the sec without specifying the number of shares or their price the company stated that they hoped to raise at least  million through the sale of shares using the money to pay off debt in full  mil