 has an  mp image sensor improved lowlight capability and records at up to  fps it was sold with three different accessory packages as the outdoor motorsports and surf editions heroedit in late  gopro announced the hero line of cameras these new cameras came in three editions black silver and white all three versions of the hero come in a new  smaller and  lighter package with wifi functionality built in the change of the physical dimensions of the cameras compared to the previous generations hero and hero were physically identical means that some of the camera accessories for hd hero original and hero are not compatible with hero so gopro made new versions of those accessories specifically for hero and mostly for hero see below those new versions of accessories are usually not compatible with older hero camera generations however a lot of other accessories are compatible with all hd hero camera generations the hero silver and black cameras have significantly less battery endurance than the hd hero original and hero for example in p resolution with  fps while hd hero original and hero have a stated battery runtime of  hours hero silver edition has a stated battery runtime of  hours and hero black edition has a stated battery runtime of  hours the black editions most economical setting is p fps so this also partially contributes to its poor battery runtime the black editionnot in citation given has a new  mp sensor that can capture k uhd digital video at  fps k video at  fps p at  fps p at  fps p at  fps p at  fps and wvga at  fps the black edition also includes the wifi remote the black edition cannot record at  fps in p and wvga resolutions it can only record at very fast frame rates in those resolutions this is a deliberate firmware limitation as the manufacturer does not expect that this highend camera model will be used at these lower resolutions and frame rates the silver edition uses the same  mp sensor as the hero and the white edition uses the same  mp sensor as the hd hero original heroedit play media a timelapse recording one frame every  seconds with a gopro hero camera mounted on a bicycle helmet during a bike ride in chicago note how the wide angle lens allows for the rider to capture wide images in october  gopro released the hero available in black and silver editions replacing the hero generation the hero white edition remains as gopros lowend device the hero camera models claim dramatically improved low light performance and have a waterproof enclosure which is  lighter and  smaller than the heros according to the gopro website the hero camera housing is  smaller than the hero the cameras are claimed to have improved image sharpness close focus down to  vs about  ft on the hero at the expense of distant focus which is slightly less sharpclarification needed with hero and better audio functionality with wind noise reduction battery life is claimed to be  longer than for the hero model both through better efficiency and a highercapacity battery of the same dimensions the black edition has video modes of p p p and p as well as k and k and can shoot mp stills at up to  fps along with the increased resolution the hero black edition also offers an optional function in firmware called superview which increases the field of view it has additional functions including dynamic low light situation adjustment higherquality recording modes higher bitrates no white balance applied etc etc the black edition continues to include a wifi remote it does not have the ability to record  fps in p and wvga modes it can only record at very fast frame rates in those lower resolutions this is an intentional firmware limitation as the manufacturer does not expect a camera with its capabilities to be used at low resolution and frame rate the battery runtime of hero black edition is significantly longer than hero black edition but – lower than the battery runtime of the older hero and hero the silver edition has video modes of p and p and can shoot mp stills at up to  fps in contrast to the black edition the silver edition can record at  fps or higher in all supported resolutions hero silver edition also has about  longer battery runtime during recording than hero black edition they both use the same batteries the difference in runtime depends on the resolutionfps combination and whether wifi and gopro mobile application are used during recording the difference in runtime increases as the fps is lowered and the additional functions are deactivated on both cameras the battery runtime of hero silver edition is similar to the battery runtime of hero and hero the hero hd camera was awarded the  technology  engineering emmy award for its contribution to television heroedit gopro hero  silver edition in september  gopro announced the hero available in black edition and silver edition which replace their respective hero generation predecessors the hero session a budget camera was also announced the hero black edition still has a  mp cmos and a f fixed maximum aperture and focus free it adds bluetooth connectivity highlight tag protune available for photo and a new processor claimed by gopro to be twice as fast as that of the hero black edition doubling the frame rates in most resolutions the hero black edition can record k uhd video × at a frame rate of   and  fps in superview mode k is only possible at  fps many other rates and resolutions are available the hero black edition still shoots stills at a maximum of mp with a maximum burst rate of  fps with wifi disabled at k gopro claims the hero black edition battery life to be  minutes increasing to a maximum of h  at p the hero black battery is in a different form factor than its predecessors initial sidebyside comparisons of hero and hero black edition video results suggest that the newer model has more detail at long range and similar performance at close range the hero silver edition is basically a hero black edition with the addition of a micro speaker builtin touch screen display protune for photo and highlight tag the first gopro with this a lower clocked cortexa and missing the black editions integrated analogtodigital converter which supports a wider variety of professional lowsensitivity external mics the video modes supported by the hero silver edition are similar to those of the hero black due to the higher processing speed and thermal requirements of k video × but it supports wifi bluetooth and contains the same ambarella inc a soc as in the hero black the hero session released july   is  smaller and  lighter comparing to other versions of the gopro hero camera the hero models maintain the h video codec of previous versions and mp file formats gopro claims the mono microphone in both the black and silver editions has twice the dynamic range of the hero and that the hero black and silver editions have improved lowlight performance model hero session hero silver hero black sensor size    aperture f f f dimensions  x  x  mm  x  x  mm  x  x  mm weight  g  g  g with case  g  g with case still image resolution  mp  mp  mp video modes p p p p k k p p p k k p p p p photo burst fps fps fps connectivity wifi bluetooth wifi bluetooth wifi bluetooth water resistance  m  m with case  m with case touchscreen no  inches  mm x optional extra herolcdedit in june  the company started to sell a new camera gopro herolcd which provides video recording at p at  fpsand  megapixel photos gopro herolcd has a touch screen to preview the shot to frame the scene perfectly and letting user easily navigate the menu new feature in the camera instant camera editing gopro herolcd is waterproof because it is built directly into a waterproof case waterproof to  feet  m the device also includes a feature hilight tagging and builtin video editing function which allows user to put a label on the main points while shooting video or in the process of view which makes it possible to quickly find desired footage later technical specifications vide