sedit as of october update gopro sells three fixedlens cameras two without viewfinders and one including a touchscreen viewfinder a bit lcd on the front of the camera allows access to its menu system which is controlled by the front and top shutter buttons the hero black have dimensions of  mm ×  mm ×  mm and weighs  grams  grams with housing still images from  to  megapixels can be captured the cameras are sold with a clear polycarbonate hd housing with a glass lens that is rated shockproof and waterproof to  feet  m with a quickrelease buckle on the top and threads at the bottom to attach to all of the gopro mounts the housing has metal buttons that connect to the cameras controls and has a skeleton backdoor option to allow audio recording when the camera is used with a mount but without the need to be watertight or shockproofnonprimary source needed productsedit hero camerasedit mmedit the mm camera model  became available on april   it had dimensions of  by  inches  by  mm and weighed  pounds  g it included the camera a clear case with quick release a camera strap and ski glove adapter lash it could pivot on the fly and be functional to a depth in water of about  feet  m it was described as a reusable wrist camera and included a roll of  exposure kodak  film digitaledit the digital hero released in  model sq minicam had a × camera and shot vga definition x fps video for a maximum of  seconds the digital hero had  mb internal memory without sd slot digital edit the digital hero released in  had a megapixel camera and shot standard definition × video it was rated up to  m  feet in depth digital edit the digital hero was first introduced on december   it had a megapixel still photo sensor and supported standard definition × video capture it ran on two aaa batteries had  mb of internal memory and could function with a  gb sd card its housing was rated to  ft meters depth its dimensions were  ×  ×  inches  ×  ×  mm the camera is not designed to work with the newer hd