ilver edition has a stated battery runtime of  hours and hero black edition has a stated battery runtime of  hours the black editions most economical setting is p fps so this also partially contributes to its poor battery runtime the black editionnot in citation given has a new  mp sensor that can capture k uhd digital video at  fps k video at  fps p at  fps p at  fps p at  fps p at  fps and wvga at  fps the black edition also includes the wifi remote the black edition cannot record at  fps in p and wvga resolutions it can only record at very fast frame rates in those resolutions this is a deliberate firmware limitation as the manufacturer does not expect that this highend camera model will be used at these lower resolutions and frame rates the silver edition uses the same  mp sensor as the hero and the white edition uses the same  mp sensor as the hd hero original heroedit play media a timelapse recording one frame every  seconds with a gopro hero camera mounted on a bicycle helmet during a bike ride in chicago note how the wide angle lens allows for the rider to capture wide images in october  gopro released the hero available in black and silver editions replacing the hero generation the hero white edition remains as gopros lowend device the hero camera models claim dramatically improved low light performance and have a waterproof enclosure which is  lighter and  smaller than the heros according to the gopro website the hero camera housing is  smaller than the hero the cameras are claimed to have improved image sharpness close focus down to  vs about  ft on the hero at the expense of distant focus which is slightly less sharpclarification needed with hero and better audio functionality with wind noise reduction battery life is claimed to be  longer than for the hero model both through better efficiency and a highercapacity battery of the same dimensions the black edition has video modes of p p p and p as well as k and k and can shoot mp stills at up to  fps along with the increased resolution the hero black edition also offers an optional function in firmware called superview which increases the field of view it has additional functions including dynamic low light situation adjustment higherquality recording modes higher bitrates no white balance applied etc etc the black edition continues to include a wifi remote it does not have the ability to record  fps in p and wvga modes it can only record at very fast frame rates in those lower resolutions this is an intentional firmware limitation as the manufacturer does not expect a camera with its capabilities to be used at low resolution and frame rate the battery runtime of hero black edition is significantly longer than hero black edition but – lower than the battery runtime of the older hero and hero the silver edition has video modes of p and p and can shoot mp stills at up to  fps in contrast to the black edition the silver edition can record at  fps or higher in all supported resolutions hero silver edition also has about  longer battery runtime during recording than hero black edition they both use the same batteries the difference in runtime depends on the resolutionfps combination and whether wifi and gopro mobile application are used during recording the difference in runtime increases as the fps is lowered and the additional functions are deactivated on both cameras the battery runtime of hero silver edition is similar to the battery runtime of hero and hero the hero hd camera was awarded the  technology  engineering emmy award for its contribution to television heroedit gopro hero  silver edition in september  gopro announced the hero available in black edition and silver edition which replace their respective hero generation predecessors the hero session a budget camera was also announced the hero black edition still has a  mp cmos and a f fixed maximum aperture and focus free it adds bluetooth connectivity highlight tag protune available for photo and a new process